<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="UTF-8" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
		<link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css" />
		<link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/icons/favicon.ico" />
		<title>PiperStorage</title>
	</head>
	<body>
		<%- include('partials/header') %>
		<main class="index">
			<section class="hero">
				<div class="heroLeft">
					<h1 class="indexTitle">PiperStorage</h1>
					<p class="indexDescription">
						A <span class="minimal">minimal </span>file storage application.
					</p>
					<% if (currentUser) {%>
						<button class="signUpBtn" onclick="window.location.href = '/home'">
						Home
					</button>
						
					<%} else {%>
							<button class="signUpBtn" onclick="window.location.href = '/signup'">
						Get started
					</button>
						
					<%}%>
					
				</div>
				<img
					class="heroImg"
					src="/images/servers.jpg"
					alt="gilfoyle and dinesh holding a laptop standing in front on PiperStorage servers"
				/>
			</section>
			<section class="about">
				<p class="aboutSubtitle">About</p>
				<p class="aboutDesc">
					PiperStorage is a next-generation, cloud-native binary artifact
					ingestion and persistence layer delivering frictionless, zero-latency
					payload orchestration across your entire distributed data ecosystem —
					leveraging chunked multipart upload pipelines, idempotent exactly-once
					delivery semantics, and edge-validated CRC32 checksum integrity
					verification to ensure every blob, object, and byte-stream is
					atomically committed to your preferred S3-compatible object storage
					backend with full end-to-end TLS 1.3 encryption, OpenTelemetry-native
					observability, and webhook-driven event emission that slots seamlessly
					into any CI/CD toolchain, ETL consumer, or microservices mesh without
					a single point of failure, vendor lock-in, or unnecessary friction
					standing between your users and their uploaded assets.
				</p>
			</section>
		</main>

		<%- include('partials/footer') %>
	</body>
</html>
